snippet.textDisplay: In response to Ben Solo becoming one with the Force, I think that it's more of a result of the acceptance of passing on and letting go rather than a learned skill. Leia couldn't let herself TRULY become one with the Force until her son had been redeemed, Luke didnt become one with the Force until he was sure that Rey would carry on the Jedi legacy to make a better galaxy, and Yoda & Obi-Wan both became one with the Force only after realizing and understanding that Luke would carry the Jedi Order onward after their deaths. Qui Gon was possibly one of the wisest characters in Star Wars when it came to accepting fate and maintaining harmony with the Force, so his ascendance to Force ghost-hood wasn't totally unexpected. And at the end of Return of the Jedi, Anakin was finally redeemed and knew that his son would do great things, as he had already done what many thought impossible: he brought out the good inside Darth Vader, and returned him to the light. With all this background in mind, Ben Solo finally redeeming himself and becoming one with the Force isnt a stretch. He knew that his mother and father, despite all he had done, still loved him, and that by saving Rey he had endured that the future his parents died for didn't turn to dust on the sandy desert floor of Tatooine.
